    <dict>
        <key>cell</key>
        <string>PSGroupCell</string>
        <key>footerText</key>
        <string>
Enable MessageSwiper:
Turns MessageSwiper On or Off.
Default:On

Custom SwipeSettings:
Makes all of the settings below have an effect. If off, default values are used.
Default:Off

Flip Swipe Directions:
Normally, swipe right to move up the list and left to go down. This reverses that behavior.
Default:Off

Enable Wrap Around:
If you're at the top of the list, you will be able to continue swiping to the right and the next conversation will be the last one in the list. Ditto for bottom -> top.
Default:Off

Enable Long Swipes:
Enables and disables long swipe functionality. Long swipe right returns to conversation list and long swipe left sends you to the newest message, which is great for reading a message that you just received.
Default:On

Enable Previews:
Enables and disables the preview bubble that shows the next message as you swipe.
Default:On

Hide Back Button:
Shows/Hides the "messages" button at the top left of the screen when viewing a conversation. Only works if Enable Long Swipes is also ON. This is purely for aesthetics.
Default:Off

Update On Send:
If On, this updates the list of conversations whenever you send a message. Which means after you send a message, you will be magically transported to the top of the list. If off, the list of conversations you swipe through will stay constant until you return to the conversation list.
Default:Off

Short Swipe Distance:
"Points" are essentially pixel values. On non-Retina devices, this translates to exact pixels. On Retina devices, this should be doubled to equate pixels. All iPhones have a width of 320 points, regardless of screen size.
Default:40

Long Swipe Distance:
Ditto for above.
Default:220


        </string>
